<H1><FONT COLOR="#333399">Data Policies</FONT></H1>

<HR ALIGN=LEFT>

<p>
Policies applying to some or all of the BADC data holdings are listed below.
For conditions of access applying to the data, please refer to the
<a href="./rules.html">Data Access Rules</a> web page.
</p>

<b>General data policies and licences:</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/conditions/badc_anon.html">BADC Terms and Conditions</a> (HTML page)
    &#151; liability disclaimer applying to data distributed through the BADC.
<li><a href="http://badc.nerc.ac.uk/data/NERC_Handbookv2.2.pdf">NERC Data Policy Handbook</a>
    (PDF document from the NERC website).
<li><a href="./BADC_Model_Data_Policy.pdf">BADC Model Data Policy</a> (PDF document)
    &#151; applying to the archival, review and distribution of model results and
    synthesized datasets.
<li><a href="./surface/met-nerc_agreement.html">NERC-Met Office Agreement</a>
    (HTML page) &#151; applying to Met Office datasets distributed through the BADC
    and to derived products (e.g. trajectories).
</ul>

<b>Conditions of use applying to particular Met Office and ECMWF datasets distributed via the
   BADC:</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/conditions/ukmopum.html">Met Office Ported Unified Model Agreement</a>
    (HTML page).
<li><a href="./era/ecmwf_era_agreement.html">Conditions of Use of ERA Re-analysis Data </a>
    (HTML page) &#151; applying to the ERA-15 and ERA-40 datasets.
<li><a href="./ecmwf-op/ecmwf_op_agreement.html">Conditions of Use of ECMWF Operational Data </a>
    (HTML page).
</ul>

<b>NERC programmes and projects data policies:</b>

<p>
These are specific to each programme or project and comply with the
<a href="http://badc.nerc.ac.uk/data/NERC_Handbookv2.2.pdf">NERC Data Policy</a>
(see above).
They are available from each individual programme or project webpage at BADC.
</p>

<b>Other datasets:</b>

<p>
Datasets issued from partner agencies (such as ESA, NASA, etc.) or by non-NERC
research activities (e.g. European Integrated Projects) will have their own
data policies, which are available from the individual project webpages at BADC.
</p>

</BODY>
</HTML>
